==English==

===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
From Latin ''[[vocalis]]'', voiced.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-vowel.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#In [[phonetics]], a sound produced by the [[vocal chords]] with relatively little restriction of the [[oral cavity]], forming the prominent sound of a [[syllable]].
#A [[letter]] representing the sound of vowel; in English, the vowels are ''a'', ''e'', ''i'', ''o'' and ''u'', and, in some cases, ''y''.

